* ion-content tag should have padding to get default padding,
	<ion-content paddding></ion-content>

* Buttons and Basic Styling
	ion-button directive converts normal HTML button to ionic styled button.
	Styles - outline / clear / round
	Button Position - block : Changes button from inline element to Block element with rounded edges
			  full : Block, full size button without rounded edges(remove padding from ion-content when using this)
	Can add icons inside buttons using ion-icon attribute inside button
	If Icon only use icon-only attribute in button
	If Icon and text mixed then use icon-left or icon-right attribute

* Lists and Styling
	Created using <ion-item> or <button ion-item> inside <ion-list> OR can also use without <ion-list> if horizontal separator is not needed.
	Placing elements:
		1. item-left or item-right can be used to move items.
			<ion-item>
			   <ion-icon name="star" item-right></ion-icon>
			</ion-tem>
		2. <ion-item> can have <h1> and <p> tags and using them together will automatically visible like title and subtitle.

	Styling:
		1. no-lines attribute in <ion-list> removes separator lines.
		2. use <ion-item-group> instead of <ion-list> to create groups.
			<ion-item-group>
				<ion-item-divider>A</ion-item-divider>
				<ion-item>Apple</ion-item>
				<ion-item-divider>B</ion-item-divider>
				<ion-item>Banana</ion-item>
			</ion-item-group>
		3. <ion-list-header> inside <ion-list> can be used to provide a header.	

* Grid System
	Created using <ion-row> then <ion-col> inside <ion-grid>
	To keep empty space from right use offset-<Value> in <ion-col>
	To keep width, use with-<value> attribute in <ion-col>

* Gestures
	Click listener - Fires in both sort and long presses 
	Tap listerner - Only fires in short presses
	Press listener - Only Fires in long presses

* Creating own components
	1. Export a normal ts class with Component declarator.
	2. Add the styling in template
	3. Add selector : 'app-<component_name>'
	4. Register in declarations in app.component.ts
	5. Use component in desired place using app-<component_name> tag in HTML


		


